Arbor Day is a day for Americans to recognize the importance of forests and woodlands in supporting the economy, health, and environment. The article highlights the contributions of trees to our way of life and encourages reflection on the sacrifices made during difficult times. The First Lady and President planted a maple tree on the South Lawn of the White House to symbolize growth and hope for future generations. The article also emphasizes the importance of preserving forests and announces the United States' participation in the One Trillion Trees Initiative. The initiative aims to restore, grow, and better manage one trillion trees worldwide by 2030. The efforts will lead to cleaner air and water, wildlife habitat creation, and a commitment to conserving nature's beauty. The article concludes with a quote from President Theodore Roosevelt, emphasizing the role of citizens in preserving forests.